$ Oracle: instance recovery
@ instance recovery

*Instance recovery* takes place when an → development/databases/Oracle/architecture/instance is re-started after a failure or a
→ development/databases/Oracle/architecture/instance/startup-shutdown[`shutdown abort`].

Instance recovery is performed by → development/databases/Oracle/architecture/processes/background/SMON[`SMON`].

The *active* → development/databases/Oracle/architecture/database/files/online-redo-log-files[online redo log files] contains the data that is required for instance recovery.

? Phases: cache recovery, transaction recovery

sa:
  → development/databases/Oracle/adminstration/backup-recovery/recovery
